to teach me how to behave like a human.

408
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:08,800
No, I haven't.

409
00:26:11,240 --> 00:26:13,340
So, in the first lesson,

410
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:18,040
you've just taken human form and still carry your beastly nature.

411
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:20,160
Though it can be brutal,

412
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:25,720
it also makes you lower your guard and obey unconditionally.

413
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:29,160
You're too sincere and kind.

414
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:31,040
That won't do you any good.

415
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:34,020
What should I do?

416
00:26:38,380 --> 00:26:42,160
Ru Ling. Teach me, please.

417
00:26:43,950 --> 00:26:45,880
Miss, we have great tube whistles.

418
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:48,200
Come have a look. Which one do you like?

419
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:50,020
Come have a look.

420
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:56,160
You have keen eyes, miss.

421
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:57,880
This tube whistle has an excellent tone.

422
00:26:57,880 --> 00:27:00,720
- How much? 
 - Only 100 gems.

423
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:03,040
- 100 gems. 
 - Yes.

424
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:04,760
Wait.

425
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:07,800
I can tell this tube whistle

426
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:10,240
was bought in bulk from South Mountain.

427
00:27:10,240 --> 00:27:11,920
It's worth no more than ten gems.

428
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:13,440
Ten gems.

429
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:16,120
Miss, you should take this one instead.

430
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:17,880
Ten gems for you.

431
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:19,000
Ten it is.

432
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:22,690
No. I'll lose money. No way.

433
00:27:22,690 --> 00:27:25,360
Wait. You can have this for ten gems.

434
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:27,400
All yours.

435
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:36,040
There you go. Master, this is my gift as a disciple.

436
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:39,720
The sound of this whistle travels a hundred li.

437
00:27:39,720 --> 00:27:44,440
If I call for you with it, you'll hear me even from afar.

438
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:49,660
All right. If you need me,
I can appear by your side anytime.

439
00:27:49,660 --> 00:27:51,960
Thank you, Nian Jiu.

440
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:59,480
You see, human minds are complicated.

441
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:01,760
Full of traps.

442
00:28:01,760 --> 00:28:04,960
If you ever come across a situation like with the whistle peddler,

443
00:28:04,960 --> 00:28:07,980
never agree so easily like you did just now. Understood?

444
00:28:07,980 --> 00:28:10,860
How should I refuse them?

445
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:14,980
I'll teach you.

446
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:20,740
You can refuse politely by saying, "This doesn't look right."

447
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:22,280
This doesn't look right.

448
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:27,800
If the other person insists, you say, "I don't have the time."

449
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:29,520
I don't have the time.

450
00:28:29,520 --> 00:28:35,900
If they still insist, you can be more direct and give a firm refusal.

451
00:28:35,900 --> 00:28:37,740
"No, I can't."

452
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:39,840
Oh, I see.

453
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:44,680
It's the same when Grandmaster
usually says, "Get lost", right?

454
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:50,640
Yes, but that's the ultimate form of rejection.

455
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:55,460
This doesn't look right. I don't have the time.

456
00:28:55,460 --> 00:28:58,280
No, I can't. Get lost.

457
00:28:58,280 --> 00:29:00,980
I think I've got the hang of it.

458
00:29:00,980 --> 00:29:04,560
I didn't teach you the last one.

459
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:07,000
This doesn't look right.

460
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,720
No, I can't. I don't have the time.

461
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:12,989
 

